{"type":"message","id":"73525928","parentId":"3d9be8f1","timestamp":"2026-03-17T20:52:01.766Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking \"Kommt das hier an?\" which means \"Is this coming through?\" or \"Is this arriving here?\" \n\nThey're probably testing if messages are being received. Since I just sent a failed Telegram message in the heartbeat and now they're asking if messages are coming through, I should respond affirmatively and acknowledge that I received their message.\n\nThis seems like a simple connectivity check. I should say \"Ja\" or something similar to confirm.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Ja, kommt an! ✅\n\nIch sehe dich laut und deutlich. Liegt am Heartbeat-Ping vorher — da war ein Config-Problem mit dem Chat-Ziel. Aber direkte Nachrichten funktionieren!"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama_cloud","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773780716764}}
